WEBVTT

00:00:00.880 --> 00:00:05.679
Jesus said, as recorded at Matthew 11.27,

00:00:05.679 --> 00:00:09.160
no one fully knows the Father,

00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:11.359
except the Son,

00:00:11.359 --> 00:00:17.059
and anyone to whom the Son is willing to reveal Him.

00:00:17.059 --> 00:00:19.660
This teaches us two things.

00:00:19.660 --> 00:00:25.600
First, that it is possible for us to know the Father fully.

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:31.839
And second, that Jesus is the key to knowing Jehovah.

00:00:31.839 --> 00:00:37.740
Jesus clearly identified his role in revealing the Father.

00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:40.240
On his last night here on Earth,

00:00:40.240 --> 00:00:46.079
he told his apostles as recorded at John 146,

00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:50.320
I am the way and the truth and the life.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:56.619
No one comes to the Father except through me.

00:00:56.619 --> 00:01:00.960
Only through Jesus can we truly know the Father

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:04.500
and have an approved relationship with Him.

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.799
Earlier at the Transfiguration,

00:01:07.799 --> 00:01:11.159
Jehovah confirmed Jesus' pivotal role

00:01:11.159 --> 00:01:14.500
when he instructed Peter James and John

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:18.000
to listen to Jesus.

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:19.840
For over a century,

00:01:19.840 --> 00:01:22.319
the fateful and discreet slave

00:01:22.319 --> 00:01:25.799
has provided a wide range of study aids

00:01:25.799 --> 00:01:29.280
to help us learn about the life, ministry,

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:32.599
and teachings of Jesus Christ.

00:01:32.599 --> 00:01:36.280
These gifts enrich our study of God's Word.

00:01:36.280 --> 00:01:40.439
They shed light on the world he lived in.

00:01:40.439 --> 00:01:43.760
The places he walked.

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:47.510
The towns where he preached.

00:01:47.510 --> 00:01:50.989
The landscapes he saw.

00:01:50.989 --> 00:01:53.629
The foodie ate.

00:01:53.629 --> 00:01:59.430
And even the seasons in which various events took place.

00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:04.189
These printed publications are more than just words on a page.

00:02:04.189 --> 00:02:07.109
They illuminate Jesus' personality

00:02:07.109 --> 00:02:09.389
and reveal his qualities,

00:02:09.389 --> 00:02:13.270
which mirror those of his Heavenly Father.

00:02:13.270 --> 00:02:16.509
We learn about Jesus' compassion,

00:02:16.590 --> 00:02:21.389
self-sacrifice, humility, power,

00:02:21.389 --> 00:02:25.590
boldness, courage, and love.

00:02:27.110 --> 00:02:28.710
More importantly,

00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:32.150
focusing on Jesus' teachings and example,

00:02:32.150 --> 00:02:35.990
draws closer to the one who sent Him.

00:02:35.990 --> 00:02:38.550
Our meetings, assemblies, and conventions

00:02:38.550 --> 00:02:43.550
also deepen our love and appreciation for God's Son.

00:02:43.789 --> 00:02:45.669
In more recent years,

00:02:45.669 --> 00:02:48.990
Jehovah's Organization has used video

00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:53.990
to reach the hearts of all those attending our conventions.

00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:59.030
But how can we continue to help honest-hearted ones

00:02:59.030 --> 00:03:03.629
to understand Jesus' role as King and High Priest

00:03:03.629 --> 00:03:07.270
and to help them acquire the mind of Christ?

00:03:08.629 --> 00:03:13.229
Well, bringing events of Jesus' ministry to life on screen

00:03:13.229 --> 00:03:18.229
or the printed page is not without its challenges.

00:03:20.699 --> 00:03:22.860
As you know, the governing body

00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:26.020
had those full-costum dramas for years at conventions

00:03:27.020 --> 00:03:30.539
that never was Jesus depicted.

00:03:30.539 --> 00:03:33.139
And you can understand the challenge

00:03:33.139 --> 00:03:34.860
who's gonna play Jesus.

00:03:34.860 --> 00:03:38.699
Can you imagine trying to select brothers

00:03:38.699 --> 00:03:43.699
in, say, 200, 300, even more different places

00:03:44.780 --> 00:03:47.219
to play the role of Jesus Christ?

00:03:47.219 --> 00:03:49.219
But then finally, for a certainty,

00:03:49.219 --> 00:03:52.780
he made him Lord and Christ, part one, part two.

00:03:52.780 --> 00:03:54.539
We went ahead, governing body,

00:03:54.539 --> 00:03:56.819
proved it, go ahead, let's have that.

00:03:56.819 --> 00:03:58.139
And it worked very well.

00:03:58.139 --> 00:04:01.219
When you see Jesus with the woman

00:04:01.219 --> 00:04:04.939
that had a flow of blood and the tenderness in our video

00:04:04.939 --> 00:04:08.780
of Jesus dealing with that woman and her fear

00:04:08.780 --> 00:04:11.620
and yet her confidence that she could be healed by Him

00:04:11.620 --> 00:04:13.500
and the way Jesus treated her,

00:04:14.460 --> 00:04:17.579
that conveyed something that we would not always bring up

00:04:17.579 --> 00:04:19.740
in our imagination.

00:04:19.740 --> 00:04:23.100
So once we saw the reaction from the brothers and sisters,

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:26.579
how their hearts were touched by this presentation,

00:04:26.579 --> 00:04:29.259
we could see this is a very effective way

00:04:29.259 --> 00:04:31.259
to portray Jesus' teachings.

00:04:31.259 --> 00:04:34.259
What could boost your spirituality more

00:04:34.259 --> 00:04:37.500
than actually seeing the scriptures come alive?

00:04:38.379 --> 00:04:43.220
But now, here is a very exciting announcement.

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:48.620
The governing body is pleased to announce

00:04:48.620 --> 00:04:52.779
that a very special video series about Jesus

00:04:52.779 --> 00:04:54.699
is currently being developed.

00:04:55.699 --> 00:04:58.980
Work is underway to develop and produce

00:04:58.980 --> 00:05:03.980
a new live action dramatic series on Jesus Christ.

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:07.860
The title of the series is,

00:05:07.860 --> 00:05:11.220
the good news according to Jesus.

00:05:12.379 --> 00:05:15.259
This series will combine the strengths

00:05:15.259 --> 00:05:19.300
of all our preceding research and study tools

00:05:19.300 --> 00:05:23.779
with the power of the moving image

00:05:23.779 --> 00:05:25.699
and will enable the viewer to gain

00:05:25.699 --> 00:05:30.699
an even deeper understanding of Jesus' life and ministry,

00:05:31.300 --> 00:05:35.100
which in turn increases our knowledge of Jehovah.

00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:39.860
Although other religious and commercial institutions

00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:44.180
have produced various films on the life of Jesus,

00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:46.019
these have often been tainted

00:05:46.019 --> 00:05:48.740
by unscriptural views of Jesus,

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:53.740
or they have placed excessive emphasis on violence

00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:59.339
and existing video productions focus on one Bible book

00:05:59.339 --> 00:06:03.819
at a time, or only on specific episodes

00:06:03.819 --> 00:06:05.660
of Jesus' ministry on earth.

00:06:06.620 --> 00:06:09.939
The good news according to Jesus, however,

00:06:09.939 --> 00:06:14.620
will show all the events of Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John

00:06:14.620 --> 00:06:17.420
in the order in which they happened,

00:06:17.420 --> 00:06:20.740
and in as much of the rich detail,

00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:25.220
as current research and Bible understanding will allow.

00:06:26.300 --> 00:06:28.699
Often a presentation like the one

00:06:28.699 --> 00:06:33.540
you're about to see is shown after a feature-linked drama

00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:35.180
is released.

00:06:35.180 --> 00:06:39.139
Such behind-the-scenes videos help us to understand

00:06:39.139 --> 00:06:44.139
and appreciate various facets of the video-making process.

00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:49.500
Today, however, we are giving you a preview,

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:53.699
a first look at an upcoming convention project

00:06:53.699 --> 00:06:56.019
that will take years to complete.

00:06:56.980 --> 00:07:00.420
In view of the large scope of this project,

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:04.459
we encourage you to make it a matter of earnest prayer

00:07:04.459 --> 00:07:09.860
to Jehovah and please support it

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:13.220
according to your circumstances.

00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:19.480
Would you like to see what episode one might look like?

00:07:19.480 --> 00:07:21.879
To provide an advanced impression of the look

00:07:21.879 --> 00:07:24.160
and feel of an episode,

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:28.160
audio video services prepare storyboards.

00:07:29.160 --> 00:07:31.480
We're pleased to share with you now

00:07:31.480 --> 00:07:50.079
an excerpt from an animated storyboard.

