was about to come into the world.

00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:10.899
Of course, this is not the final video.

00:10:11.899 --> 00:10:16.899
Rather, it's an example of how the words on a page

00:10:16.899 --> 00:10:18.659
can come to life.

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:23.379
Preparing simple basic drawings to convey the idea

00:10:23.379 --> 00:10:27.700
of a video is one of the early visual tools

00:10:27.740 --> 00:10:30.220
used during the approval process.

00:10:31.139 --> 00:10:35.740
The animatic review is a very early milestone

00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:38.259
for the visual storytelling.

00:10:39.220 --> 00:10:41.940
But how has the project been developed?

00:10:42.899 --> 00:10:45.700
What direction has the governing body given

00:10:45.700 --> 00:10:49.259
for bringing events in Jesus' life to the screen?

00:10:50.860 --> 00:10:54.620
So first of all, the governing body approved the concept

00:10:54.620 --> 00:10:56.980
of producing a production like this.

00:10:57.980 --> 00:10:59.899
But there were some questions.

00:10:59.899 --> 00:11:00.980
How do you do it?

00:11:01.820 --> 00:11:05.179
So three options were given to the governing body.

00:11:05.179 --> 00:11:08.059
The first option was for us just to have

00:11:08.059 --> 00:11:10.899
a theatrical stage production,

00:11:10.899 --> 00:11:13.620
similar to what we'd already done.

00:11:13.620 --> 00:11:18.620
The second set of options involved having a narrator speak

00:11:20.179 --> 00:11:23.259
and just read the sections of Scripture

00:11:23.259 --> 00:11:25.419
and in the background to have acting,

00:11:25.419 --> 00:11:28.259
but not actually to have Jesus speaking

00:11:28.259 --> 00:11:31.460
or those involved with Jesus speaking.

00:11:32.299 --> 00:11:34.340
And then finally, the third option,

00:11:34.340 --> 00:11:36.659
which is, of course, the hardest

00:11:36.659 --> 00:11:41.659
and involves a lot of work is to do a real life drama.

00:11:42.539 --> 00:11:45.220
So we were interested to see how the governing body

00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:46.980
would feel about this.

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:49.740
And what a joyous time it was to see the brothers say,

00:11:49.740 --> 00:11:52.460
we want the best for the brotherhood.

00:11:52.460 --> 00:11:56.539
We want them to be able to see the power and impact

00:11:56.539 --> 00:11:58.299
of what Jesus taught.

00:11:58.299 --> 00:12:00.500
Yes, we want the third option.

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:04.059
So then we realized there's a lot of work ahead.

00:12:04.059 --> 00:12:08.220
It's easy to think the inspired text is there,

00:12:08.220 --> 00:12:10.059
what's to write.

00:12:10.059 --> 00:12:13.419
But it's not as simple as just taking a little half hour

00:12:13.419 --> 00:12:15.899
chunks out of the four gospel accounts

00:12:15.899 --> 00:12:19.340
and throwing them on script and filming them.

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:21.740
Which gospel account do you use?

00:12:21.740 --> 00:12:24.379
Do you use Matthew's account, Mark's, Luke's?

00:12:24.379 --> 00:12:27.620
So very quickly, we saw the need to lay each

00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:31.700
of the four gospel accounts side by side

00:12:31.700 --> 00:12:36.820
and decide which account in every case, every event

00:12:36.820 --> 00:12:40.340
gives us the fullest picture, the most details.

00:12:40.340 --> 00:12:43.259
So even if you can't say everything that appears

00:12:43.259 --> 00:12:45.740
in all four accounts, you use the one

00:12:45.740 --> 00:12:48.139
to carry the bulk of the story.

00:12:48.139 --> 00:12:50.620
The others provide the rest of the details

00:12:50.620 --> 00:12:52.139
that we'll actually see.

00:12:52.139 --> 00:12:54.940
The brothers who help write the dramas,

00:12:54.940 --> 00:12:57.899
they have a tremendous amount of work to do.

00:12:57.899 --> 00:13:00.580
But then there also are those who do the research

00:13:00.580 --> 00:13:03.059
just to make sure little details are correct,

00:13:03.059 --> 00:13:05.379
whether it be the shoes a person has on

00:13:05.379 --> 00:13:07.500
or whether he even wears shoes.

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:13.379
When you show something on film, you are committing yourself.

00:13:13.379 --> 00:13:16.740
You are saying this is the explanation.

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:19.580
Or in some cases, the application,

00:13:19.580 --> 00:13:22.379
it goes beyond illustration, it's the explanation,

00:13:22.379 --> 00:13:24.220
it's the way to understand what happened.

00:13:24.220 --> 00:13:26.860
And that is what sticks with people's memories.

00:13:26.860 --> 00:13:30.820
So it's a huge responsibility to get that right.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:34.899
So our research department already has a lot of information.

00:13:34.899 --> 00:13:39.059
But doing something like this is yet another step

00:13:39.059 --> 00:13:42.059
down the path of being very, very difficult

00:13:42.059 --> 00:13:44.620
because there are a lot more questions come up.

00:13:44.620 --> 00:13:46.179
How are we going to depict the devil?

00:13:46.179 --> 00:13:48.139
How do you show Jesus walking on water?

00:13:48.179 --> 00:13:51.820
What footwear was allowed in the soarig?

00:13:51.820 --> 00:13:53.179
And what's a soarig?

00:13:53.179 --> 00:13:56.940
Research is pivotal in this.

00:13:56.940 --> 00:14:00.100
So you make a decision about what to depict.

00:14:01.220 --> 00:14:04.259
But then there are details when it comes to

00:14:04.259 --> 00:14:08.539
not just telling it, not just reading what happened,

00:14:08.539 --> 00:14:12.419
but now that you have to show what happened,

00:14:12.419 --> 00:14:13.659
how do you do that?

00:14:13.659 --> 00:14:15.340
If you take something that's static,

00:14:15.340 --> 00:14:17.580
like a piece of artwork that's well researched,

00:14:17.580 --> 00:14:21.059
solid sources, and now you bring it to life.

00:14:21.059 --> 00:14:24.500
In many respects, more research needs to go into this

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:28.299
so that everything is looked at from various angles.

