00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:13.019
When we see how different people respond

00:17:13.019 --> 00:17:15.019
and react to Jesus' ministry,

00:17:15.019 --> 00:17:17.980
how they're shaped and molded by what the experience,

00:17:17.980 --> 00:17:20.619
that's essentially that character's arc.

00:17:20.619 --> 00:17:23.859
We go in and say, okay, where does our character start?

00:17:23.859 --> 00:17:25.339
How does he grow?

00:17:25.339 --> 00:17:28.660
And where is he by the end of this series?

00:17:28.660 --> 00:17:31.660
By seeing his struggles, seeing his challenges,

00:17:31.660 --> 00:17:33.940
it makes that character more relatable.

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:37.940
As years of development passed,

00:17:37.940 --> 00:17:42.819
the immense gop of this project came into clear focus.

00:17:42.819 --> 00:17:47.339
A natural question arose, where would we record it?

00:17:47.339 --> 00:17:50.220
When we were doing the production of Jonah,

00:17:50.220 --> 00:17:52.539
we used parts of Southern California,

00:17:52.539 --> 00:17:54.819
and we thought that would be a very good location.

00:17:54.819 --> 00:17:57.380
So that was proposed to the governing body,

00:17:57.380 --> 00:18:00.299
and they said, thank you very much,

00:18:00.299 --> 00:18:03.180
but we would rather that you use existing

00:18:03.180 --> 00:18:05.779
Bethel facilities that would be available

00:18:05.819 --> 00:18:08.859
and that maybe has not been utilized to its full potential.

00:18:08.859 --> 00:18:12.619
So we worked with worldwide design construction,

00:18:12.619 --> 00:18:16.180
and they provided a list of some of the branches that had space.

00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:18.140
And as we were doing so,

00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:21.660
it came to our attention that in Australasia,

00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:25.380
the printer was about to be phased out.

00:18:25.380 --> 00:18:30.380
At the end of 2015, the printing work was moved to Japan.

00:18:30.380 --> 00:18:32.339
The press was in put up for sale.

00:18:32.339 --> 00:18:34.619
It sold about three years later.

00:18:34.619 --> 00:18:37.019
So now we had this big warehouse space,

00:18:37.019 --> 00:18:38.700
just what we needed for a studio.

00:18:39.980 --> 00:18:44.019
We just were stunned to think that such a project

00:18:44.019 --> 00:18:45.500
could be accomplished here,

00:18:45.500 --> 00:18:49.660
but I think we've also seen so many evidences of Jehovah's blessing

00:18:49.660 --> 00:18:52.339
on this project that it's very clear

00:18:52.339 --> 00:18:53.500
it's something he wants.

00:18:53.500 --> 00:18:56.180
The temporary accommodation here at the branch

00:18:56.180 --> 00:18:58.140
was due for demolition,

00:18:58.140 --> 00:19:01.579
and I mean, like the build-ozes were almost at the gate.

00:19:01.579 --> 00:19:04.220
So we were able to stop those build-ozes,

00:19:04.220 --> 00:19:08.140
and as a result, we're currently renovating those residents.

00:19:08.140 --> 00:19:10.579
Jehovah's hem was definitely in that experience

00:19:10.579 --> 00:19:13.740
without the stopping of that demolition.

00:19:13.740 --> 00:19:15.619
We wouldn't have had enough accommodation

00:19:15.619 --> 00:19:17.500
to look after this project.

00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:21.660
It was as if Jehovah was dropping this option in our laps

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:25.940
with all the criteria that we needed to do this project.

00:19:25.940 --> 00:19:28.980
With the primary location selected,

00:19:28.980 --> 00:19:32.299
production design helps take a concept

00:19:32.299 --> 00:19:34.299
and make it a reality.

00:19:35.420 --> 00:19:37.259
Our goal as production design

00:19:37.259 --> 00:19:40.819
is to immerse the audience in the story.

00:19:40.819 --> 00:19:42.500
If they have that sense,

00:19:42.500 --> 00:19:47.299
now they're paying attention to what's being set on screen,

00:19:47.299 --> 00:19:50.180
what they can learn, what they can benefit from it.

00:19:51.779 --> 00:19:53.700
It's one thing to design something,

00:19:53.700 --> 00:19:56.819
but then to execute that design is all another thing.

00:19:56.819 --> 00:19:58.619
Even like with the throne room,

00:19:58.619 --> 00:20:00.579
this actually is too much work.

00:20:00.579 --> 00:20:02.220
We have to simplify it.

00:20:02.220 --> 00:20:04.180
Do we need to show three walls?

00:20:04.180 --> 00:20:06.539
Can we just get away with building two walls

00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:09.660
and have the same effect, the same production quality?

00:20:10.539 --> 00:20:15.660
Usually we design a set, we build a set, we fill in the set,

00:20:15.660 --> 00:20:17.579
and then we turn the set down.

00:20:17.579 --> 00:20:20.339
Put this project unique in that we're not doing that.

00:20:20.339 --> 00:20:23.420
These buildings, these structures that we're going to be filming

00:20:23.420 --> 00:20:25.779
are going to last for years.

00:20:25.779 --> 00:20:27.980
And so they have to be built that way.

00:20:28.019 --> 00:20:32.339
So how do we combine modern day building standards

00:20:32.339 --> 00:20:33.500
to make it last,

00:20:33.500 --> 00:20:36.299
but still make it look like an old ancient building

00:20:36.299 --> 00:20:38.779
that was built 2,000 years ago?

00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:41.779
We were looking for a certain type of finish,

00:20:41.779 --> 00:20:42.859
concrete finish.

00:20:42.859 --> 00:20:47.259
Through a website, we found there was a company over in Perth

00:20:47.259 --> 00:20:49.579
that was able to achieve this.

00:20:49.579 --> 00:20:52.619
And after calling them, find out their brothers.

00:20:52.619 --> 00:20:55.220
And those brothers have been able to come over

00:20:55.220 --> 00:20:57.099
and help us with their expertise

00:20:57.099 --> 00:20:59.299
to get the right type of finish.

00:20:59.299 --> 00:21:02.980
The support from all those under the Australasia branch

00:21:02.980 --> 00:21:06.700
territory has been faith strengthening.

00:21:06.700 --> 00:21:08.779
So one of the biggest needs we probably

00:21:08.779 --> 00:21:11.500
have at the moment would be auditioning.

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:15.140
We absolutely need more volunteers for acting.

00:21:15.140 --> 00:21:17.339
It's a unique and new form of sacred service

00:21:17.339 --> 00:21:20.819
is something that probably most never thought they would ever

00:21:20.819 --> 00:21:24.700
do or be asked to do, but there is definitely a need.

00:21:24.700 --> 00:21:26.619
The more that can make themselves available

00:21:26.619 --> 00:21:28.140
through this auditioning process,

00:21:28.140 --> 00:21:31.220
allows us to have the right people and the roles.

00:21:31.220 --> 00:21:35.259
One fundamental principle that underlies any good acting

00:21:35.259 --> 00:21:36.299
is empathy.

00:21:36.299 --> 00:21:37.940
It's something that we all learn as Christians.

00:21:37.940 --> 00:21:41.380
It's not about showing the behavior in big ways.

00:21:41.380 --> 00:21:43.220
It's about understanding who the character is.

00:21:43.220 --> 00:21:45.099
And then it kind of exudes naturally.

00:21:45.099 --> 00:21:47.299
Jehovah's organization will always train us

00:21:47.299 --> 00:21:51.140
and Jehovah's spirit will make us ready for the task

00:21:51.140 --> 00:21:52.579
that's ahead of us.

00:21:52.579 --> 00:21:54.140
It's simple training,

00:21:54.140 --> 00:21:56.779
but it's definitely designed to help somebody

00:21:56.779 --> 00:21:59.500
get comfortable in front of a camera,

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:01.779
performing in front of many people,

00:22:01.779 --> 00:22:04.299
and being able to relax, being able to be themselves.

00:22:04.299 --> 00:22:07.259
To see our brothers and sisters offering themselves,

00:22:07.259 --> 00:22:12.539
putting themselves out in this way is wonderful.

00:22:12.539 --> 00:22:15.339
When this project was first discussed,

00:22:15.339 --> 00:22:18.180
it kind of felt like so far into the future

00:22:18.180 --> 00:22:19.779
and almost in a possibility.

00:22:19.779 --> 00:22:24.500
It was so big in scope, but now it's actually happening.

00:22:24.539 --> 00:22:27.220
And you see Jehovah's blessing on the planning,

00:22:27.220 --> 00:22:32.579
on the construction, on the people.

00:22:32.579 --> 00:22:34.420
Will there be challenges?

00:22:34.420 --> 00:22:35.539
Oh, yeah.

00:22:35.539 --> 00:22:39.220
Guaranteed, but if Jehovah wants something done,

00:22:39.220 --> 00:22:40.420
that's what happens.

00:22:40.420 --> 00:22:42.740
We have things at the right time,

00:22:42.740 --> 00:22:44.099
and that's what we've done.

00:22:44.099 --> 00:22:46.539
We've advanced now to where we're able to do it

00:22:46.539 --> 00:22:49.019
in such a wonderful way for the whole world.

00:22:49.019 --> 00:22:51.299
We are working with the best words

00:22:51.299 --> 00:22:54.579
